result.execSummary:
The defendant Emmanuel Erickson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).
  • Negligent Operation of Motor Vehicle [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. 12:59 PM cases 21CF1290 and 22CF344 called. Prosecuting attorney Angela Lynn Beranek in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Emmanuel Erickson in court, in custody.  Attorney William Schembera in court for Emmanuel Erickson and on behalf of Matthew Krische in 21CF1290. There is an agreement which the State recites. Victim/Witness statute complied with. 
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
In 22CF344: Defendant pleads No Contest to Counts 1, 3 and 4 as charged in the Information. Defendant acknowledges prior convictions to support repeater enhancers. 
In 21CF1290: Defendant pleads No Contest to Amended Ct 1: Delivery of Methamphetamine (no enhancers). 
Court accepts pleas and finds the Defendant Guilty. Anything else is dismissed and read in. State asks restitution be set at $0. 
Court withholds sentencing and places the defendant on Probation for 4 years on each count with conditions: 
Complete AODA and follow through with recommendations. 
Maintain absolute sobriety. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
No contact with N.F., T.F., A.W., J.M. or No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting. 
No driving anyone else's vehicle without their consent. 
Pay court costs including $90 in WCDTF buy funds. 
Defendant has 47 days credit in 22CF344 and no credit in other file if revoked from Probation.
